content: Recommended the others as not to waist Never worked
How can I auto exit the app to save battery (since there is push notification...)?
replyContent: When the app is switched to background, it moves the registration to our push server and goes to sleep. This way, the app is suspended and consumes almost no power, but remains in memory and you can switch to it quickly. Auto-exit is not really needed in this situation, Android should close the app when it needs to free some memory automatically.
